g.text: Frontend
1. Microphone to read input
2. Touchscreen to inspect and confirm commands
that are running
3. A speaker of some sort to communicate verbally
with the user.
4. Some sort of authentication/some way to know
that the user is talking to them.
-> Passphrase/common phrase?
Ideal form factor seems to be a tablet or phone of
some kind, with a dedicated microphone? Could sit on
a table or mount to a wall.
Communicate with an agentic LLM that has
access to some tools and can gather info
High level requirements doc for Alfie
Possible use cases
1. Asking what the temperature is
2. Asking when the next bus is (and in which direction)
3. Asking for the next available theatre tickets (api calls?
tough one, maybe)
